results.occurrenceRemarks: This patch of Cowpen Daisy is actually part of my butterfly garden in the front yard.  The seed source for the plants was local in the Austin area.  This patch is populated (some would say "infested") with a small caterpillar which is feeding on the flower heads.  If you look carefully, you can see that the ray flowers are folded over on several of the daisies on these plants.  Another set of images will illustrate that critter, now identified as the "Sunflower Moth", Homoeosoma electella (Pyralidae, Phycitinae).
